(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[69],{318:function(e){e.exports={data:{post:{title:"Up, up, up! Down, down, down...",content:'<h3 id="2018-hasnt-been-a-very-progressive-year"><a href="#2018-hasnt-been-a-very-progressive-year" aria-hidden="true"><span class="icon icon-link"></span></a>2018 hasn’t been a very... progressive year.</h3>\n<p>After moving back from the city at the end of last year, my responsibilities and life have become rather static. I get told I do an important job and do it well, but I still feel sharply pathetic revealing what I do. Saying to someone that I look after an elderly man in a small, dead town isn’t very attractive.\n<a href="/assets/static/src/media/images/blog/AtTheBog.jpg"><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill=\'none\' viewBox=\'0 0 512 512\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\' xmlns:xlink=\'http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id=\'__svg-blur-9\'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in=\'SourceGraphic\' stdDeviation=\'40\'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x=\'0\' y=\'0\' filter=\'url(%23__svg-blur-9)\' width=\'512\' height=\'512\' xlink:href=\'data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2b4onQlvQZq24GLGwulkU99OBvAioglA/DShL%2bWgcR0bCUHA6nNedoT0FMdofCvDIfkodITtY48jDuH1pDyN3EfSkGU/4zSTIflx%2btGoinPPJ89bPXYowonjIXGPhblA88d9S/7i5JA4aUb8yuvKNh/wC61tXHv9P6X9095wzeRQKxz2EoOB6Gso1r2Q8U6ZJyvbrKucc4bIolcyw%2bng90FnCXtp1jTZIrae7kuLBXALXC9q4XvwcgnHhXQ9rq17PBHNFqVrJHIoZWFs24IyD96uTtU9nV3YcLS3rS4vIftCgOxXvHrW0eyed5fZ7or3FwFcxEYZWJwGYD9qNWtmf1dEa0pL7Zp66reIPtJ4nP5YmH/aky63egZjAbwyMfzQ9mMnPbSN/xi/2adiEbH4veseOFH%2b6JTZQ8%2bSY/EGtmKbs4bV5sfZAkgE9/N4VFuOIuIwZRBaw9oFXswU5gTj4icHOPACnZ4IFt2kjjaQKMktMc/QYqhllSRx2CqrdxyeYeY3qOeNyOWnk0NZCFGHDeWag60wS1HbBTnuXJPoBWV8LccaxrN57immMtwckSRklAB5nvoO4u4g4ju%2bIprWKSa2WElGZpuRWPrg1mt8HXpfAWe0FZJtKvreBTC7wNgMOm2d/pU/gK9sLHgLQElZBMLKMkHfqM/wA0K6LbX0unXUl9LIUaJkBaUupyMZGQDVjcwRaWsdlDbiRbaNYlPTOFAplcnHYxu7S0wT5z%2bhRNxbYI/IgJI3JC7Uw3EjSANbTQ9mTk8y5NCTSyFlX3ZVPgAKdiL4%2bHfHUZo9cjnvUmw2sdQvHcEywOhIzgb4/Sp0kNpcIJSkPOTjIXlb96AluXiBHLjPeBvTNzfzCPHvDKCc4zjFGrMbj1NY9zU%\' /%3e%3c/svg%3e" width="512" alt="At the Beach." data-srcset="/assets/static/AtTheBog.82a2fbd.f96beb6.jpg 480w, /assets/static/AtTheBog.cbda223.f96beb6.jpg 512w" data-sizes="(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px" data-src="/assets/static/AtTheBog.cbda223.f96beb6.jpg"><noscript><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded" src="/assets/static/AtTheBog.cbda223.f96beb6.jpg" width="512" alt="At the Beach."></noscript></a>\n<em>Hey! It was overcast and windy.</em>\nBut like I said before, <a href="/blog/2018/12/02/a-little-help-from-my-friends">I get by with a little help from my friends.</a> Having a circle of friends has become important to me. Crazy, I know! I manage to organize things so I seem to get away every other weekend, doing things from LAN-ing up for some vintage Halp to going to a pub.</p>\n<p>I’m still extremely awkward, but dating is more fun than hard. It’s still not an overly frequent event, though. I have pity for <a href="/blog/2017/04/11/dating-is-hard-and-i-am-very-awkward">the version of me from years ago when that first “personal” entry was posted.</a> I don’t get nervous for most things in life now, plus I’ve learned the fine art of shutting the hell up and listening rather than raving on.</p>\n<p>Some of the time at least.</p>\n<p>I am gaming much more. I picked up an Xbox One and opted to go all digital with games. Right now it’s showing 204 games installed, that many physical discs would require a small shed! I’m not sure of the legitimacy of the various key trading websites I’ve been using to buy stuff, but I like to live dangerously. I’m also using the Game Pass subscription service Microsoft offers. Picking up 6 month extensions as they’ve come on sale has got me all loaded up until sometime late 2020. Remember when that felt like an unobtainable future?</p>\n<p><a href="/assets/static/src/media/images/blog/XboxGameCount.jpg"><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill=\'none\' viewBox=\'0 0 1920 1440\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\' xmlns:xlink=\'http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id=\'__svg-blur-46\'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in=\'SourceGraphic\' stdDeviation=\'40\'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x=\'0\' y=\'0\' filter=\'url(%23__svg-blur-46)\' width=\'1920\' height=\'1440\' xlink:href=\'data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bmK4wt3C7Q3xEKOO5NNsdjERzGn%2bqwfTYdoJjQsDkEDuDS2jbIJ7RXu28Tx6ZbWy3IEIlVHOAp7tnt0pMvEnTVY4pVUSy43MnIK552t/WKpHtcifRfEsWrs6GGWFYDEAdxxk9ew%2b9Tm41qHVtRD2MEcCQRALAuVX5hkjg8/wBCmLLCWOktr%2boCLbn8BXiDEVvJEuyUgfHn5wMHoaTUii95QRtIVDAr3606eLYZ7eGaW6eJzIhUGNw21fynjNK9nCsc1o2AAzKc5PrUuXjGXTwV43cO/k3F05W8s%2bWAW7AnFHrBZd2JURR2KsSf4oDZFfKYMpYY5Ud6M6e6pjy7eVd3U4A/k1WyYOxJxWbINtecTHbxyazLnZkjB9KBmEm9vejPqWi6eLSDfP7wQzDsu09aiFvZ3WiXDxXMaI2xH2LycEnGfrgmtm/Hd/NBo06Wlo1xKVJ3IQTHgcEjrg9OKg/u093oetXLB7e490kYpICCcdx6Z9aS9J16/Qr4LSErxepNm5kbzS8ZZSiHCnr%2b4NBwIn/DNihcsuFA6DPeiy2s0t/p4a2gtyZANyuxb5T1yea7uAhe3UxKnwooKDknv96Um5aZRkVPSpGy1jcDa2WIGOq9R%2blHbG8VVwBPJ3yUP/KSNOvVSQ7mwBR621aHC7X3Z/KCatZMhyguQyA4IyOh61yS4wp7c0vxakpXg4rqXUQR1pbZtHw%2bKVlunnSK6lixCDsjjViTnGef16VN9WgEOh6woubq6bymgcSbQRuznIXpjp6U9eIbuSaxMduCzlhna4UgeuTU61e5j0%2bwv4GeLdOvlKyncZJHJwGI7D1PqaDinFpt36A7E0h02W01KF41kkMZyu984HTOPv8AzQuU%2bXexwLuSVcHknj6Ux3gmiuFkkliAiG4onPGTx09aT7y8ZWNywVmySo6Ac5rJuHKmq19Gq3tM/9k=\' /%3e%3c/svg%3e" width="1920" alt="Too Many Games." data-srcset="/assets/static/XboxGameCount.82a2fbd.3a98960.jpg 480w, /assets/static/XboxGameCount.cbab2cf.3a98960.jpg 1024w, /assets/static/XboxGameCount.2665e34.3a98960.jpg 1920w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" data-src="/assets/static/XboxGameCount.2665e34.3a98960.jpg"><noscript><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded" src="/assets/static/XboxGameCount.2665e34.3a98960.jpg" width="1920" alt="Too Many Games."></noscript></a>\n<em>The big number is daunting.</em>\nA few highlights from the experience are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://www.snake-pass.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Snake Pass:</a> Very frustrating until you figure out how to actually progress, but it’s such a beautiful game with a neat approach to traversal.</li>\n<li><a href="https://sniperelite4.com/en" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Sniper Elite 4:</a> Yes, it’s absolutely absurd. But it’s fun! Any bugs or annoying quirks from prior installments in the series have been ironed out. Testicle shots always cause me to wince.</li>\n<li><a href="https://www.sega.com/games/sonic-forces" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Sonic Forces:</a> An attempt to return to the tried and true method, after not being successful for a bit. It is the same Sonic Colours/Sonic Generations gameplay, oddly limited in scope despite attempts to put new features in like character creation. Not amazing, but I was still left wanting more. Maybe even <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9gc0169Ht48" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">One More Last First Bump.</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/halo-5-guardians/brrc2bp0g9p0?activetab=pivot:overviewtab" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Halo 5: Guardians:</a> Extremely strong mechanics, tuned almost too well.. The story got a bit… bogged down. The removal of split screen was unfortunate, largely because none of my friends are at all interested in an Xbox One. Would love to do a 4 player team to push through on Legendary difficulty, but alas.</li>\n<li><a href="https://forzamotorsport.net/en-us/games/fh4" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Forza Horizon 4:</a> I was impressed by realising how much tech must be under the hood in order to have all these different vehicles handle so well in so many different environments. Racing isn’t a high priority, my biggest time sink is blindly exploring this little bit of fictional Britain.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I still have things to get to! I really want to dive into Paper Mario: Color Splash on Wii U - having that and others in my backlog is somewhat holding me back from investing in a Switch.</p>\n<p>Sometime in the New Year, when the postal service starts to run again, I should have another budget review up. This time it’s for what I’d call the cheapest viable phone. It’s from a brand I’ve never heard of, but on paper it looks like a deal. I think I’m getting hooked to the thrill of the gamble. <a href="https://youtu.be/kzwHs9PhJwY?t=99" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">I take a chance, I roll the dice</a> and either get a great deal or dog shit.</p>\n<p>Could that be a metaphor for dating? Maybe, but it’s not very kind.</p>\n',date:"2018-12-30T00:00:00.000Z",timeToRead:26}}}}}]);